
# Docker-ci Tool.

Docker-CI is a containerized framework build on docker to
provide suitable test environment for building components
and running tests (e.g. UT, FT, Integration tests etc) in CI


## Pre-requisites
1. Hardwares to host Docker-CI tool
2. Softwares:
   a. Ubuntu 14.04 recommended (with hypervisor capabilities)
   b. Docker 17.03.0-ce recommended
   c. Docker-Compose 17.03.0-ce recommended

## Contents
Features delivered in docker-ci

NOTE: For detailed information and usage on below features refer README in corresponding directory

### Jenkins-slave

docker-ci tool has scripts to create container slaves for a particular Jenkins master.
Scaling is possible for slave containers

### SWM 1.0 flow

Supports 2+0 and 2+2 as default cluster configurations
Supports AIT way of component installation
Supports Scaling of nodes

### SWM 2.0 flow (LDEwS)

Supports 2+0 and 2+2 as default cluster configurations
Supports Scaling of nodes

### SWM 2.0 flow (LDEfS)

Supports 1+0 and 1+1 as default cluster configurations

